Cape Town - Six people, including four children, have died in a fire in Bonteheuwel on the Cape Flats.The City Of Cape Town&apos;s fire and rescue services responded to the fire at about 2am on Wednesday morning.Spokesperson Liezl Moodie said: &#x201C;Two adult females and four minor males died as a result of fatal burn wounds&#x201D;.She said the house in Netreg Street was gutted, leaving a further six people displaced. The cause of the fire is unknown at this stage. African News Agency